# SwapNest MVP — Smoke Test Improvements Plan

7 prioritized changes to prepare the MVP for a university smoke test by Friday.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Step 1 — Fix the LocalStorage Trap (Waitlist + Analytics)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Recommended tool: Google Apps Script Webhook** — 100% free, no account signup, data lands in a Google Sheet you already own. Zero dependencies, just a `fetch()` call.

**How it works:**
1. You create a Google Sheet → Extensions → Apps Script → deploy a `doPost()` web app
2. The script receives JSON and appends a row to the sheet
3. From the website, we fire a `fetch(WEBHOOK_URL, { method:'POST', body: JSON.stringify(data) })` — done

**Why this over alternatives:**
| Option | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **Google Apps Script** ✅ | Free, instant, data in a Sheet | Requires one-time 5-min setup |
| Formspree | Easy | Free tier = 50 submissions/mo |
| Make.com | Visual | Overkill, requires account |
| Netlify Forms | Nice | Only works on Netlify |

#### [MODIFY] [analytics.js](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/analytics.js)

- Add a `WEBHOOK_URL` constant at the top (placeholder until you deploy the Apps Script)
- Add a `sendToSheet(payload)` helper that `fetch`es the webhook URL with the payload
- Modify [trackWaitlistSignup()](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/analytics.js#92-107) → also call `sendToSheet({ type:'waitlist', ... })`
- Modify [trackClick()](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/analytics.js#77-91) → also call `sendToSheet({ type:'click', ... })`
- Keep localStorage as a local fallback / for the admin-metrics page — **don't remove it**

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/app.js)

- In `handleWaitlist()`, pass the name + email to the webhook via `sendToSheet`

