### Step 2 — Open Graph Meta Tags

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/index.html)

Add inside `<head>` (after existing `<meta description>`):

```html
<meta property="og:title" content="SwapNest – Move Smarter. Live Greener." />
<meta property="og:description" content="The student-focused circular moving platform. Rent, trade, donate — all in one place." />
<meta property="og:image" content="https://<YOUR_DOMAIN>/logo.png" />
<meta property="og:url" content="https://<YOUR_DOMAIN>/" />
<meta property="og:type" content="website" />
```

> [!WARNING]
> The `og:image` URL **must be an absolute HTTPS URL** — relative paths won't work on WhatsApp/Instagram. You'll need to replace `<YOUR_DOMAIN>` with the actual deployed URL (e.g. your GitHub Pages or Netlify URL).

