## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (Browser)

Since this is a static HTML/JS site with no test framework, verification is manual:

1. **Waitlist webhook** — Open [index.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/index.html) in browser, submit the waitlist form, check the Google Sheet to confirm the row appeared. Also check browser console for no errors.
2. **OG tags** — Use [opengraph.xyz](https://opengraph.xyz) or the [Facebook Sharing Debugger](https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/) with the deployed URL to verify the preview card renders correctly.
3. **Dynamic dashboard** — Create an account → make a reservation → navigate to [dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/dashboard.html) → confirm the name, avatar, and stats reflect the logged-in user, not "Anna".
4. **Social proof** — Open [index.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/index.html) and visually confirm the testimonial quote appears below the waitlist form.
5. **Waitlist placeholder** — Check the email field says "Use your university email for priority access".
6. **License checkbox** — Open the Van booking modal on [services.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/services.html) → try to submit without checking the box → confirm the browser blocks submission.
7. **Empty state** — On [marketplace.html](file:///c:/Users/niekl/OneDrive/Bureaublad/universiteit/Essentials%20of%20entrepeneurship/website/marketplace.html), apply a filter that matches no items (e.g. Kitchen filter if no kitchen items are visible) → confirm the empty-state message appears.
8. **Footer links** — Click each social link in the footer → confirm it opens the correct URL in a new tab (or stays on the correct URL).
